  "body": "**What would you like to be added**:\r\n\r\n* Currently, specifying multiple aliases for a single host using `HostAliases` results in a line for each alias in `/etc/hosts`.\r\n* Example:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  hostAliases:\r\n  - ip: \"127.0.0.1\"\r\n    hostnames:\r\n    - \"foo.local\"\r\n    - \"bar.local\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nleads to an `/etc/hosts` file containing something like \r\n\r\n```\r\n127.0.0.1 foo.local\r\n127.0.0.1 bar.local\r\n``` \r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\n\r\n* Having multiple entries for the same IP address in `/etc/hosts` can break DNS resolution for some software.  See https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/102660/hosts-file-is-it-incorrect-to-have-the-same-ip-address-on-multiple-lines for more details\r\n\r\n<!-- DO NOT EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\r\n/kind feature",
